IRS990.MissionDesc: The Museo De Las Americas is dedicated to educating our community through collecting preserving interpreting and exhibiting the diverse arts and cultures of the Americas from ancient to contemporary through innovative exhibitions and programs. These programs are guided by a culturally- responsive education model that is founded on the philosophy that fostering a student's culture and encouraging creativity are critical in setting the foundation for authentic meaningful learning experiences. The success of this approach is clear as this model has been implemented by organizations seeking diversity training for their staff. Educational programming and exhibits are at the core of Museo's mission and Museo continues to remain conscientious of its community's needs and respond to the recommendations and feedback received from its patrons and community leaders. Museo's exhibitions and programming remain innovative and relevant to an ever- expanding population.
IRS990.Desc: For the 2021-2022 fiscal year our outreach educational programs including tours and workshops served 24,492 people. With a strong return to normal scheduled programming Museo was able to serve 996 students in Title I schools with 1565 students visiting the museum and 330 students served virtually at schools. The educational programming offered through Museo de las Americas encourages exploration of the arts and cultures of Latin America. We brought our educational programming to 18 unique schools in and around the Denver metro area. Our highest numbers were in Denver County where we served 12,858 students.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Museo's Endowment Fund annual interest is disbursed once a year to Museo to General Operating Support GOS and to cover the expenses of insurance and Collections Manager salary that will be responsible for the day-to-day oversight and preservation of Museo's Collections.
Board of Trustees fills out and signs an annual conflict of interest questionnaire and originals are kept in the records of Museo.
Executive Director compensation is approved by the board of trustees.
